        <h5 id="getting-started-content"><strong><?php echo __( 'Getting started with Shelfless', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></strong></h5>
        <dl class="faq-accordion">
            <dt id="getting-started-01-content"><?php echo __( 'Does the Shelfless plugin require the WooCommerce plugin?', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></dt>
            <dd><p><?php echo __( 'Yes, the Shelfless plugin extends the WooCommerce functionalities on Wordpress, thus you need to have WooCommerce installed, activated and set up properly before you can use Shelfless for WooCommerce.', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></p></dd>

            <dt id="getting-started-02-content"><?php echo __( 'What are other technical requirements needed to install and use the Shelfless for WooCommerce?', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></dt>
            <dd>
                <p><?php echo __( 'Below are the minimum system requirements needed by Shelfless for WooCommerce:', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></p>
                <ul class="list-disc">
                    <li><?php echo __( 'Wordpress 5.x onwards', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></li>
                    <li><?php echo __( 'WooCommerce 5.x onwards', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></li>
                    <li><?php echo __( 'PHP 7.4 and above (may be used with PHP 8.x dependent on its compatibility of Wordpress)', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></li>
                    <li><?php echo __( 'Support for TLS 1.2 and above', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></li>
                    <li><?php echo __( 'Any modern browser', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></li>
                </ul>
                <p><?php echo __( 'Additionally, the Shelfless for WooCommerce plugin has been tested to work with PHP 8.0.x.', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></p>
            </dd>
        </dl>

        <h5 id="fulfillment-content"><strong><?php echo __( 'Fulfillment', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></strong></h5>
        <dl class="faq-accordion">
            <dt id="fulfillment-01-content"><?php echo __( 'Why aren\'t the sales orders fulfilled automatically?', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></dt>
            <dd><?php echo __( 'In general, for Shelfless to automatically fulfill the orders, the products must be enabled to be fulfilled. Go to <strong>Shelfless -> Products & Stocks -> Fulfill & Sync</strong> tab, under <strong>Fulfill column</strong>, then select/enable the checkbox of the products you want to be fulfilled by Bring. This checkbox can also be seen on the product page under the tab Inventory. In product level, go to <strong>Products -> Select and Edit Product -> Inventory</strong> tab -> check/enable the <strong>Enable Fulfillment with Shelfless</strong>.', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></dd>
        </dl>

        <h5 id="article-synchronization-content"><strong><?php echo __( 'Article Synchronization', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></strong></h5>
        <dl class="faq-accordion">
            <dt id="article-synchronization-01-content"><?php echo __( 'How can I automatically synchronize creation and update of products from my platform to Shelfless?', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></dt>
            <dd>
                <p><?php echo __( 'In general, for Shelfless to automatically sync the articles, the products must be enabled to be sync\'ed. Go to <strong>Shelfless -> Products &amp; Stocks -> Products</strong> tab, select/enable the checkbox for <strong>Synchronize Products</strong>.', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></p>
                <p><?php echo __( 'Also, go to <strong>Shelfless -> Products & Stocks -> Fulfill & Sync</strong> tab, under <strong>Sync column</strong>, select/enable the checkbox.', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></p>
                <p><?php echo __( 'In product level, go to <strong>Products -> Select and Edit Product -> Inventory</strong> tab -> check/enable the <strong>Enable Article Sync with Shelfless</strong>.', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></p>

                <div class="hint-rad imp-note">
                    <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" role="presentation"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M12 22C9.34784 22 6.8043 20.9464 4.92893 19.0711C3.05357 17.1957 2 14.6522 2 12C2 9.34784 3.05357 6.8043 4.92893 4.92893C6.8043 3.05357 9.34784 2 12 2C14.6522 2 17.1957 3.05357 19.0711 4.92893C20.9464 6.8043 22 9.34784 22 12C22 14.6522 20.9464 17.1957 19.0711 19.0711C17.1957 20.9464 14.6522 22 12 22V22ZM12 11.375C11.6685 11.375 11.3505 11.5067 11.1161 11.7411C10.8817 11.9755 10.75 12.2935 10.75 12.625V15.75C10.75 16.0815 10.8817 16.3995 11.1161 16.6339C11.3505 16.8683 11.6685 17 12 17C12.3315 17 12.6495 16.8683 12.8839 16.6339C13.1183 16.3995 13.25 16.0815 13.25 15.75V12.625C13.25 12.2935 13.1183 11.9755 12.8839 11.7411C12.6495 11.5067 12.3315 11.375 12 11.375ZM12 9.96875C12.4558 9.96875 12.893 9.78767 13.2153 9.46534C13.5377 9.14301 13.7188 8.70584 13.7188 8.25C13.7188 7.79416 13.5377 7.35699 13.2153 7.03466C12.893 6.71233 12.4558 6.53125 12 6.53125C11.5442 6.53125 11.107 6.71233 10.7847 7.03466C10.4623 7.35699 10.2812 7.79416 10.2812 8.25C10.2812 8.70584 10.4623 9.14301 10.7847 9.46534C11.107 9.78767 11.5442 9.96875 12 9.96875Z" fill="rgb(10, 88, 202)"></path></svg>
                    <p class="mb-0"><?php echo __( 'Though it was mentioned here that articles can be synchronized with Shelfless automatically, the mechanism behind it involves cron actions (called Action Scheduler on WooCommerce). Depending on how the heartbeat cron is set up on the server where your storefront is hosted, it may take some time (usually 30 minutes to an hour) for products to be fully synchronized.', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></p>
                </div>
                <div class="hint-rad imp-note">
                    <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" role="presentation"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M12 22C9.34784 22 6.8043 20.9464 4.92893 19.0711C3.05357 17.1957 2 14.6522 2 12C2 9.34784 3.05357 6.8043 4.92893 4.92893C6.8043 3.05357 9.34784 2 12 2C14.6522 2 17.1957 3.05357 19.0711 4.92893C20.9464 6.8043 22 9.34784 22 12C22 14.6522 20.9464 17.1957 19.0711 19.0711C17.1957 20.9464 14.6522 22 12 22V22ZM12 11.375C11.6685 11.375 11.3505 11.5067 11.1161 11.7411C10.8817 11.9755 10.75 12.2935 10.75 12.625V15.75C10.75 16.0815 10.8817 16.3995 11.1161 16.6339C11.3505 16.8683 11.6685 17 12 17C12.3315 17 12.6495 16.8683 12.8839 16.6339C13.1183 16.3995 13.25 16.0815 13.25 15.75V12.625C13.25 12.2935 13.1183 11.9755 12.8839 11.7411C12.6495 11.5067 12.3315 11.375 12 11.375ZM12 9.96875C12.4558 9.96875 12.893 9.78767 13.2153 9.46534C13.5377 9.14301 13.7188 8.70584 13.7188 8.25C13.7188 7.79416 13.5377 7.35699 13.2153 7.03466C12.893 6.71233 12.4558 6.53125 12 6.53125C11.5442 6.53125 11.107 6.71233 10.7847 7.03466C10.4623 7.35699 10.2812 7.79416 10.2812 8.25C10.2812 8.70584 10.4623 9.14301 10.7847 9.46534C11.107 9.78767 11.5442 9.96875 12 9.96875Z" fill="rgb(10, 88, 202)"></path></svg>
                    <p class="mb-0"><?php echo __( 'For updates, only product name and product description may be pushed and synchronized to Shelfless.', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></p>
                </div>
                <div class="hint-rad imp-note">
                    <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" role="presentation"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M12 22C9.34784 22 6.8043 20.9464 4.92893 19.0711C3.05357 17.1957 2 14.6522 2 12C2 9.34784 3.05357 6.8043 4.92893 4.92893C6.8043 3.05357 9.34784 2 12 2C14.6522 2 17.1957 3.05357 19.0711 4.92893C20.9464 6.8043 22 9.34784 22 12C22 14.6522 20.9464 17.1957 19.0711 19.0711C17.1957 20.9464 14.6522 22 12 22V22ZM12 11.375C11.6685 11.375 11.3505 11.5067 11.1161 11.7411C10.8817 11.9755 10.75 12.2935 10.75 12.625V15.75C10.75 16.0815 10.8817 16.3995 11.1161 16.6339C11.3505 16.8683 11.6685 17 12 17C12.3315 17 12.6495 16.8683 12.8839 16.6339C13.1183 16.3995 13.25 16.0815 13.25 15.75V12.625C13.25 12.2935 13.1183 11.9755 12.8839 11.7411C12.6495 11.5067 12.3315 11.375 12 11.375ZM12 9.96875C12.4558 9.96875 12.893 9.78767 13.2153 9.46534C13.5377 9.14301 13.7188 8.70584 13.7188 8.25C13.7188 7.79416 13.5377 7.35699 13.2153 7.03466C12.893 6.71233 12.4558 6.53125 12 6.53125C11.5442 6.53125 11.107 6.71233 10.7847 7.03466C10.4623 7.35699 10.2812 7.79416 10.2812 8.25C10.2812 8.70584 10.4623 9.14301 10.7847 9.46534C11.107 9.78767 11.5442 9.96875 12 9.96875Z" fill="rgb(10, 88, 202)"></path></svg>
                    <p class="mb-0"><?php echo __( 'When you create a product, some information may or may not be shown and synchronized on Shelfless. Examples of information are dimensions and weights, as these are to be measured at the warehouse using precision instruments. The actual dimensions and weight measured at the warehouse will always prevail and will be used in shipping.', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></p>
                </div>
            </dd>

            <dt id="article-synchronization-02-content"><?php echo __( 'How will I know the number of products I have on Shelfless?', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></dt>
            <dd>
                <p><?php echo __( 'You may log in to your Shelfless portal account to check the current products (called Articles in Shelfless portal). You may also check the products found by the Shelfless for WooCommerce plugin under the <strong>Shelfless -> Products & Stocks -> Fulfill & Sync</strong> tab. There should be a column shown in the grid named "Shelfless" with two possible values: "Found" and "Not Found".', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></p>
            </dd>

            <dt id="article-synchronization-03-content"><?php echo __( 'The product is not syncing with Shelfless systems?', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></dt>
            <dd>
                <p><?php echo __( 'Make sure you have published the article. If the article is published but still not syncing (e.g. you don\'t see it in the portal) contact customer service.', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></p>
            </dd>

            <dt id="article-synchronization-04-content"><?php echo __( 'I want to sync a new product to Shelfless warehouse but I don\'t what it to be published in my store – how do I do?', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></dt>
            <dd>
                <p><?php echo __( 'For a product to be synced from your store to Shelfless warehouse it needs to be published. Sometimes though you like to syncronize the product before you start to sell it so Shelfless can receive it at the warehouse. Instead of publishing it in your store, you create the product in the Shelfless portal to syncronize with the Shelfless\' warehouse management system (WMS). It will not be syncronized with your store. It is important that the product in the portal and your store looks the same so it is not conflicting later when you publish the version in your store.', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></p>
            </dd>
        </dl>

        <h5 id="shipping-content"><strong><?php echo __( 'Shipping', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></strong></h5>
        <dl class="faq-accordion">
            <dt id="shipping-01-content"><?php echo __( 'How do I enable shipping with Shelfless for WooCommerce?', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></dt>
            <dd>
                <p><?php echo __( 'Go to <strong>Products -> Select and Edit Product -> Shipping</strong> tab -> check/enable the <strong>Ship with Shelfless</strong>.', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></p>
            </dd>
            <dt id="shipping-02-content"><?php echo __( 'How can I map my current shipping methods shown to customers at checkout to what is approved in my Shelfless contract?', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></dt>
            <dd>
                <p><?php echo __( 'You can set flat rates and free shipping methods to map to specific shipping methods and carriers approved in your contract by going to <strong>Shelfless -> Shipping -> Shipping Mappings</strong> tab.', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></p>
            </dd>
            <dt id="shipping-03-content"><?php echo __( 'How can I map which order statuses I need for Shelfless to start fulfilling at the warehouse?', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></dt>
            <dd>
                <p><?php echo __( 'Go to <strong>Shelfless -> Orders -> Status Mappings</strong> tab. On this page, you can also set which order statuses you want the fulfilled/processed/ship orders to be set to once Shelfless has started processing your fulfillment.', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></p>
            </dd>
            <dt id="shipping-04-content"><?php echo __( 'How to setup Shelfless Delivery?', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></dt>
            <dd>
                <p><?php echo __( 'Go to <strong>Shelfless -> Shipping -> Shipping Delivery</strong> tab. By using Shelfless Delivery, your customers will be able to choose Bring shipping services on checkout. Make sure you <strong>add and enable Shelfless Delivery</strong> as a shipping method on your WooCommerce shipping zones.', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></p>
                <p><?php echo sprintf( __( 'For more detailed view, you may refer to %s section of the user guide tab.', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ), '<a href="?page=bring_3pl_shelfless_fulfillment_for_woocommerce_help&userguide=shelfless_delivery#shelfless-delivery"><strong>Shelfless delivery</strong></a>' ); ?></p>

            </dd>
            <dt id="shipping-05-content"><?php echo __( 'How to add and enable Shelfless Delivery?', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></dt>
            <dd>
                <p><?php echo __( 'Go to <strong>WooCommerce -> Shipping -> Shipping zones</strong> tab. Click on a specific zone, and under <strong>Shipping method</strong> section, click on <strong>Add shipping method</strong> and manually select <strong>Shelfless Delivery</strong> method from the dropdown and then hit <strong>Add shipping method</strong> button save the changes.', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></p>
                <p><?php echo sprintf( __( 'For more detailed view, you may refer to %s section of the user guide tab.', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ), '<a href="?page=wc-settings&tab=shipping"><strong>Enable Shelfless Delivery in WooCommerce Shipping Settings</strong></a>' ); ?></p>
            </dd>
        </dl>

        <h5 id="out-of-stock-products-content"><strong><?php echo __( 'Out-of-Stock Products', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></strong></h5>
        <dl class="faq-accordion">
            <dt id="out-of-stock-products-01-content"><?php echo __( 'Will I be notified if a product is out of stock at the Shelfless warehouse?', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></dt>
            <dd>
                <p><?php echo __( 'You can opt to see Wordpress notifications on your administrative dashboard if one or more products are out of stock at the warehouse. A notice will be shown on top of the page. However, this will only show if you enable notifications if products are seen by Shelfless to be out of stock.', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></p>
            </dd>

            <dt id="out-of-stock-products-02-content"><?php echo __( 'How to enable the notifications for out-of-stock products?', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></dt>
            <dd>
                <p><?php echo __( 'Go to <strong>Shelfless -> Products & Stocks -> Stocks</strong> tab, enable the checkbox for "Show Admin Notification If a Product is Out of Stock".', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></p>
            </dd>

            <dt id="out-of-stock-products-03-content"><?php echo __( 'Does Shelfless support partial deliveries due to out-of-stock products?', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></dt>
            <dd>
                <p><?php echo __( 'No. If one or more products is out of stock, the whole order will wait until the affected product is restocked at the warehouse. If you don\'t want to wait, you can remove the product from the affected order with an out-of-stock product and then the order will be fulfilled in the next transmission of update.', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></p>

                <div class="hint-rad alert-note">
                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" fill="rgb(251, 162, 63)" class="bi bi-exclamation-triangle-fill" viewBox="0 0 16 16">
                        <path d="M8.982 1.566a1.13 1.13 0 0 0-1.96 0L.165 13.233c-.457.778.091 1.767.98 1.767h13.713c.889 0 1.438-.99.98-1.767L8.982 1.566zM8 5c.535 0 .954.462.9.995l-.35 3.507a.552.552 0 0 1-1.1 0L7.1 5.995A.905.905 0 0 1 8 5zm.002 6a1 1 0 1 1 0 2 1 1 0 0 1 0-2z"/>
                    </svg>
                    <p class="mb-0"><?php echo __( 'Orders with out-of-stock products may not be transmitted to the Shelfless warehouse and may not be visible to Shelfless portal, but instead held on to the Shelfless Order Control System. You can easily identify if this is the case because affected orders will be moved to a separate status called "Backordered on Shelfless."', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></p>
                </div>
            </dd>
        </dl>

        <h5 id="backorder-workflows-content"><strong><?php echo __( 'Backorder Workflows', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></strong></h5>
        <dl class="faq-accordion">
            <dt id="backorder-workflows-01-content"><?php echo __( 'What is the process flow of orders marked as "Backordered at Shelfless"?', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></dt>
            <dd>
                <p><?php echo __( 'This is the situation when the stock is insufficient at the warehouse for one or more products in an order, therefore, it cannot be fulfilled at the current time. The affected order will have its status changed to "Backordered on Shelfless" as a result. However, the order will be fulfilled automatically once the stocks are available at the warehouse.', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></p>
            </dd>

            <dt id="backorder-workflows-02-content"><?php echo __( 'I see a "Backordered by Shelfless" status on my orders. What does that mean?', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></dt>
            <dd>
                <p><?php echo __( 'A "Backordered on Shelfless" status means that the warehouse does not have enough stocks to fulfill one or more items in the order at the moment, and the order is temporarily put on hold until stocks have been replenished in the warehouse. Currently, Shelfless does not ship orders partially, and so the entire order will be affected. Once stocks have been updated and there are enough to fulfill the order, it will be automatically processed without further actions from the merchant. Corresponding movements of the order will be recorded by the Shelfless plugin on the Order Notes section of the Order Details page.', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></p>

                <div class="hint-rad alert-note">
                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" fill="rgb(251, 162, 63)" class="bi bi-exclamation-triangle-fill" viewBox="0 0 16 16">
                        <path d="M8.982 1.566a1.13 1.13 0 0 0-1.96 0L.165 13.233c-.457.778.091 1.767.98 1.767h13.713c.889 0 1.438-.99.98-1.767L8.982 1.566zM8 5c.535 0 .954.462.9.995l-.35 3.507a.552.552 0 0 1-1.1 0L7.1 5.995A.905.905 0 0 1 8 5zm.002 6a1 1 0 1 1 0 2 1 1 0 0 1 0-2z"/>
                    </svg>
                    <p class="mb-0"><?php echo __( 'Backordered orders may not be transmitted to the Shelfless warehouse and may not be visible to Shelfless portal, but instead held on to the Shelfless Order Control System. It will move to other statuses once actions are being effected into the order, like when there is enough stock to finally fulfill the order.', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></p>
                </div>
            </dd>

            <dt id="backorder-workflows-03-content"><?php echo __( 'Can I cancel an order that is marked "Backordered by Shelfless"?', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></dt>
            <dd>
                <p><?php echo __( 'Yes, you can. Move the order to a status that triggers a Shelfless cancellation and the plugin will send a cancellation request on your behalf. There will be a corresponding note added to the Order Notes section of the Order Details page.', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></p>

                <div class="hint-rad imp-note">
                    <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" role="presentation"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M12 22C9.34784 22 6.8043 20.9464 4.92893 19.0711C3.05357 17.1957 2 14.6522 2 12C2 9.34784 3.05357 6.8043 4.92893 4.92893C6.8043 3.05357 9.34784 2 12 2C14.6522 2 17.1957 3.05357 19.0711 4.92893C20.9464 6.8043 22 9.34784 22 12C22 14.6522 20.9464 17.1957 19.0711 19.0711C17.1957 20.9464 14.6522 22 12 22V22ZM12 11.375C11.6685 11.375 11.3505 11.5067 11.1161 11.7411C10.8817 11.9755 10.75 12.2935 10.75 12.625V15.75C10.75 16.0815 10.8817 16.3995 11.1161 16.6339C11.3505 16.8683 11.6685 17 12 17C12.3315 17 12.6495 16.8683 12.8839 16.6339C13.1183 16.3995 13.25 16.0815 13.25 15.75V12.625C13.25 12.2935 13.1183 11.9755 12.8839 11.7411C12.6495 11.5067 12.3315 11.375 12 11.375ZM12 9.96875C12.4558 9.96875 12.893 9.78767 13.2153 9.46534C13.5377 9.14301 13.7188 8.70584 13.7188 8.25C13.7188 7.79416 13.5377 7.35699 13.2153 7.03466C12.893 6.71233 12.4558 6.53125 12 6.53125C11.5442 6.53125 11.107 6.71233 10.7847 7.03466C10.4623 7.35699 10.2812 7.79416 10.2812 8.25C10.2812 8.70584 10.4623 9.14301 10.7847 9.46534C11.107 9.78767 11.5442 9.96875 12 9.96875Z" fill="rgb(10, 88, 202)"></path></svg>
                    <div class="note-contents">
                        <p><?php echo __( 'As a rule: only orders having the current statuses below can be requested for cancellation or update (like adding or removing items in an order):', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></p>
                        <ul class="list-disc mb-0">
                            <li><?php echo __( 'Fulfillment Processed by Shelfless', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></li>
                            <li><?php echo __( 'Backordered on Shelfless', 'bring-3pl-shelfless-fulfillment-for-woocommerce' ); ?></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </dd>
        </dl>

    </div>
</div>
